{"questionId":"9076413","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Rocket A and rocket B are travelling in opposite directions from the Earth along the same&nbsp;straight line.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4751/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-12_om_16.33.49.png\" alt=\"M18/4/PHYSI/SP3/ENG/TZ2/03\"></p>\n<p>In the reference frame of the Earth, the speed of rocket A is 0.75<em>c </em>and the speed of rocket B&nbsp;is 0.50<em>c</em>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate, for the reference frame of rocket A, the speed of rocket B according to the&nbsp;Lorentz transformation.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong><em>ALTERNATIVE 1</em></strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"u' = \\frac{{(0.50 + 0.75)}}{{1 + 0.5 \\times 0.75}}c\">\n  <msup>\n    <mi>u</mi>\n    <mo>′</mo>\n  </msup>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n      <mn>0.50</mn>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>0.75</mn>\n      <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>0.5</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>0.75</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>0.91<em>c</em></p>\n<p><strong><em>ALTERNATIVE 2</em></strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"u' = \\frac{{ - 0.50 - 0.75}}{{1 - ( - 0.5 \\times 0.75)}}c\">\n  <msup>\n    <mi>u</mi>\n    <mo>′</mo>\n  </msup>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>0.50</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>0.75</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>0.5</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>0.75</mn>\n      <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>–0.91<em>c</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076413","referenceCode":"18M.3.SL.TZ2.3a.ii","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Calculate, for the reference frame of rocket A, the speed of rocket B according to the Lorentz transformation.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity (Core topics)","A.2 – Lorentz transformations","Option A: Relativity","Option A: Relativity (Core topics)"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}